extends layout

block content
	h1= title
	p Welcome to #{title}
	br
	p Here you can learn about 4 different web vulnerabilities

	dir.lessonPanel
		h2
			a(href="lessons/sql/1") SQL injections
		a(href="lessons/sql/1")
			p.
				SQL injection is a code injection technique, 
				used to attack data driven applications, 
				in which malicious SQL statements are inserted into an 
				entry field for execution (e.g. to dump the database contents to the attacker)
	dir.lessonPanel
		h2
			a(href="lessons/directObj/1") Insecure Direct Object References 
		a(href="lessons/directObj/1")
			p.
				A direct object reference occurs when a developer exposes a reference to an internal
				implementation object, such as a file, directory, or database key. Without an access 
				control check or other protection, attackers can manipulate these references 
				to access unauthorized data